<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-08-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-08-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="681" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d681">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Moore</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Cambon</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-08-19"><hi rend="italic">August
                                        19, 1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">Personal.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: Referring to your oral
                            request, I have now the pleasure to transmit herewith, for the files of
                            your embassy, a typewritten copy in English of the peace protocol signed
                            August 12, 1898, of the President’s order directing the Secretary of
                            State to sign that instrument, and of the President’s proclamation.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Moore.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>